"title": "7382: house of God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7382: house of god",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The place where God was seen to dwell with his people, initially the tabernacle and subsequently the temple at Jerusalem.</p>\n<h2>Early references to the house of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:16-Gen28:17\">GEN 28:16–28:17</a></strong> <em>“house of God” was first used by Jacob to commemorate the place where he met with God</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:19\">GEN 28:19</a></strong> <em>“Bethel” means “house of God”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:22\">GEN 28:22</a></p>\n<h2>The tabernacle as the house of God</h2>\n<h3>The tabernacle was referred to as such before its construction</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:19\">EXO 23:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:26\">EXO 34:26</a></p>\n<h3>In the wilderness God said he would dwell with his people in the tabernacle</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:8-Exod25:9\">EXO 25:8–25:9</a></strong></p>\n<h3>God's presence came and dwelt in the tabernacle when it was completed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:33-Exod40:34\">EXO 40:33–40:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:35-Exod40:38\">EXO 40:35–40:38</a></p>\n<h2>The temple as the permanent house of God</h2>\n<h3>David's desire to build the LORD a permanent house</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:1-2Sam7:2\">2SA 7:1–7:2</a></strong></p>\n<h3>This was not the LORD's will for David</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:5-2Sam7:7\">2SA 7:5–7:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:12-2Sam7:13\">2SA 7:12–7:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:45-Acts7:47\">ACT 7:45–7:47</a></p>\n<h3>Solomon builds the temple in Jersualem</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:4-1Kgs5:5\">1KI 5:4–5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:1-1Kgs6:2\">1KI 6:1–6:2</a></p>\n<h3>God's presence dwelt there but was conditional upon the faithfulness of the people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:10-1Kgs8:13\">1KI 8:10–8:13</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:11-2Chr6:2\">2CH 5:11–6:2</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:6-1Kgs9:9\">1KI 9:6–9:9</a></p>\n<h2>Zerubbabel's temple referred to as the house of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra1:5\">EZR 1:5</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra2:68\">EZR 2:68</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra3:8-Ezra3:9\">EZR 3:8–3:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra3:11\">EZR 3:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra4:24\">EZR 4:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra5:2\">EZR 5:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra5:13\">EZR 5:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra5:16-Ezra5:17\">EZR 5:16–5:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:1\">EZR 10:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:6\">EZR 10:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:9\">EZR 10:9</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh6:10\">NEH 6:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:16\">NEH 8:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:32\">NEH 10:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:34-Neh10:38\">NEH 10:34–10:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh11:11\">NEH 11:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh11:22\">NEH 11:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:40\">NEH 12:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:9\">NEH 13:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:11\">NEH 13:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:14\">NEH 13:14</a></p>\n<h2>Other names given to the house of God</h2>\n<h3>Sanctuary</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:8\">EXO 25:8</a></p>\n<h3>House of prayer</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:13\">MAT 21:13</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:17\">MRK 11:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:46\">LUK 19:46</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa56:7\">ISA 56:7</a></p>\n<h3>God's dwelling-place</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:45-Acts7:47\">ACT 7:45–7:47</a></p>\n<h2>The need for due reverence in worship</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:1\">ECC 5:1</a></p>\n<h2>The house of God under the new covenant</h2>\n<h3>In the hearts of God's people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:16\">1CO 3:16</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:6\">GAL 4:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:48\">ACT 7:48</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:24\">ACT 17:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:19\">1CO 6:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:22\">2CO 1:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:16\">2CO 6:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:17\">EPH 3:17</a></p>\n<h3>In the church, the body of Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:6\">HEB 3:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:19-Eph2:22\">EPH 2:19–2:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:4-1Pet2:5\">1PE 2:4–2:5</a></p>",
